Nathan Valsalva "Nathan the hook" (1915-1949) was born a male in Venice, Italy and a well known, criminal, terrorist, and mafia member . His mother is Melissa Valsalva, a massage therapist (age 35). He has no father, as his father was unknown. He has a family Persian cat named Juno. During his early childhood he was known for his rudeness and his violence. At his later childhood he was known for his crimes. Around 14 and 17 he committed murderer against two people his younger brother and his Italian Teacher. Around September 17th, 1949 he got killed by his gang members after accusing somebody for being a rat, from his suspicious acts, getting beated along suffering massive injuries.

== Early life ==
At age 1, his mother married his new stepfather 38-year old receptionist named Agosto Vespucci. At age 3, his mother and step-father had a baby boy named Diego. At age 5, he was angry at his father for giving him a box of carrots instead of a box of donuts so he bit his throat. At age 6, he got enrolled into Gravity Primary School. At age 10 his cat passed away, from eating rancid fish that was left in the trash. At age 11, he started dating a girl named Emilia Toscani, a few months after that he started pickpocketing and other crimes. At age 14, Nathan did the most unpredictable thing while playing  baseball with his brother Diego, he scared him by dressing up like a angry Karen and a few hours later he unfortunaly passed away, at age 11. His funeral was a couple days after his death, his parents thought it was a natural death. At age 15, Nathan got diagnosed with depression, knowing killing his brother was for the best. At age 16, he no longer suffered from depression. At age 17, while at class he poured antifreeze into his Italian teacher, Mr. Baresi's iced tea, and killed him the cops came to the scene and arrested Nathan and he was sentenced for life, of his 2 counts of murder. At age 18, he got out of prison and decided to apply for the Venice Mafia.

